<h2>
    Oregon Fishing Regulations You Need to Know (2025)
</h2>
<p>
    Before heading out, familiarize yourself with the latest fishing rules from the <strong>Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife (ODFW)</strong>:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>License:</strong> A valid Oregon angling license is required. If fishing for salmon, you also need a Combined Angling Tag.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Daily Limits:</strong> Typically 2 adult salmon per day (check river-specific rules).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Hatchery vs. Wild:</strong> Only <strong>hatchery Coho</strong> (with clipped adipose fin) may be retained.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Barbless Hooks:</strong> Mandatory in certain areas like the Columbia River.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Seasonal Closures:</strong> Some rivers or sections close during parts of the run to protect spawning fish.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Always consult the <strong>ODFW Recreation Report</strong> for up-to-date info.
</p>
